00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.360
1557 Blower and Thermodisc Installation

00:00:03.850 --> 00:00:08.890
Welcome to this addition of Burn Tech
University presented by United States Stove Company

00:00:09.010 --> 00:00:13.250
in today's video we willl show you how to
properly install

00:00:13.250 --> 00:00:16.789
the blower and thermodisc on your 1557

00:00:16.789 --> 00:00:20.000
furnace always refer to your owner's
manual

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:23.310
this video is for informational purposes
only

00:00:23.310 --> 00:00:27.440
if you are unsure about replacing any of
the components on the stove we recommend

00:00:27.440 --> 00:00:29.340
having a certified electrician

00:00:29.340 --> 00:00:32.640
or stove technician do this for you

00:00:32.640 --> 00:00:37.890
the tools needed for today's project
are wire stripers needle nose pliers

00:00:37.890 --> 00:00:41.950
5/16ths drill or socket driver quarter
inch ratchet

00:00:41.950 --> 00:00:45.470
six-inch extension flathead screwdriver

00:00:45.470 --> 00:00:48.820
and a number 2 Phillips screw driver

00:00:49.140 --> 00:00:52.940
Installing the Thermodisc

00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:57.430
To attach the thermodisc put the part in
place then insert and tighten

00:00:57.430 --> 00:01:04.430
the screws with the drill

00:01:05.420 --> 00:01:07.860
to attach the conduit remove the lock nut

00:01:08.280 --> 00:01:13.010
bend and break the metal tabs on the connector
plugs

00:01:13.340 --> 00:01:17.720
attach the connector plugs by using your
wire strippers to clamp the plugs to the

00:01:17.720 --> 00:01:21.080
wires from the conduit

00:01:21.080 --> 00:01:24.550
inserts the conduit into the bottom of the thermodisc cover

00:01:24.550 --> 00:01:28.430
then replace and tighten the lock nut

00:01:28.430 --> 00:01:33.030
plug the two connector plugs onto the
thermodisc

00:01:33.030 --> 00:01:36.570
place the cover over the thermodisc and
using your drill

00:01:36.570 --> 00:01:43.570
insert and tighten the screws holding the
cover to the back of the stove

00:01:43.960 --> 00:01:48.540
Installing the blowers

00:01:49.149 --> 00:01:51.690
remove the cover for the wires on the
side of the blowers

00:01:51.690 --> 00:01:55.090
using your number 2 Phillips
screw driver

00:01:55.090 --> 00:02:00.410
straighten the wires out of the box then
use your flat head screwdriver to remove the knockout

00:02:01.870 --> 00:02:05.280
slide the clip nuts over the
openings on the back the stove

00:02:05.280 --> 00:02:08.050
where the blower will mount

00:02:08.050 --> 00:02:11.700
now place the gasket around the opening

00:02:11.700 --> 00:02:15.409
while holding the gasket place the
blower onto the back of the stove

00:02:15.409 --> 00:02:19.409
now insert and tighten the bolts to secure
the blower you'll need to repeat these

00:02:19.409 --> 00:02:26.409
steps to install the second blower

00:02:27.520 --> 00:02:30.480
Installing the Junction box

00:02:30.930 --> 00:02:33.330
next attach the mounting plate to the
back of the stove

00:02:33.330 --> 00:02:40.069
by lining the holes up. Then insert and
tighten the screws using your drill

00:02:40.069 --> 00:02:43.459
before you mount electrical junction
box to the mounting plate

00:02:43.459 --> 00:02:48.419
remove the knockouts you will need to remove one of the top for the thermodisc wires

00:02:48.580 --> 00:02:52.640
two on the left hand side for the power
cord and blower wire.

00:02:52.640 --> 00:02:55.260
then one on the right hand side for the other blower
wire

00:02:55.269 --> 00:03:00.149
install the junction box to the mounting plate by inserting then tightening the screws

00:03:01.930 --> 00:03:05.299
remove the lock nut  from the conduit coming from the thermodisc

00:03:05.299 --> 00:03:09.599
place the connection through the knockout you removed on the top of the junction box

00:03:09.750 --> 00:03:16.750
after the conduit is in place replace the lock nut and tighten

00:03:18.700 --> 00:03:22.400
Wiring in your junction box

00:03:23.320 --> 00:03:26.020
insert the conduit into the blower and replace the lock nut

00:03:26.220 --> 00:03:29.360
bring the conduit from the blower to the conduction box

00:03:29.360 --> 00:03:36.360
the replace and tighten the lock nut. Do the same for the second blower

00:03:51.579 --> 00:03:54.909
locate your power cord and place the
black clip around it

00:03:54.909 --> 00:04:00.509
Pres the clip then push the power cord
through the opening on the left hand side of the junction box

00:04:03.730 --> 00:04:07.100
it is now time to connect all the wiring in
the junction box

00:04:07.100 --> 00:04:11.110
the green wire which is the ground wire
coming from the power cord

00:04:11.110 --> 00:04:18.110
should be fastened to the back of the
junction box by a screw

00:04:21.609 --> 00:04:24.790
connect the black wire from the power
cord and the white

00:04:24.790 --> 00:04:31.790
wire coming from the thermodisc using a
wire nut

00:04:34.520 --> 00:04:37.910
next connect the black wire coming from
the thermodisc

00:04:37.910 --> 00:04:42.910
to the black wire coming from the left
and right blower using a wire nut

00:04:51.419 --> 00:04:55.020
lastly connect to white wire from the
power cord

00:04:55.020 --> 00:04:59.480
to the white wires coming from the left
and right blower with a wire nut

00:05:13.059 --> 00:05:19.080
going to the blowers strip the tips of
the wires on both blowers

00:05:19.080 --> 00:05:25.480
connect the wire coming from the blower
to the white wire coming from the conduit using a wire nut

00:05:35.970 --> 00:05:38.550
next connect the black wire coming from
the blower

00:05:38.550 --> 00:05:45.550
to the black wire coming from the
conduit using a wire nut

00:05:51.270 --> 00:05:55.050
replace the cover then insert and
tighten the screws to secure it

00:05:55.050 --> 00:05:59.730
you will need to do this for both
blowers slide the junction box cover into place

00:05:59.840 --> 00:06:04.160
then tighten the screws to hold the
cover on

00:06:04.160 --> 00:06:09.600
Now that your project is complete connect  power to your stove and check for proper operation

